50|$|In a <b>forensic</b> <b>autopsy</b> or Post-mortem examination, body of {{deceased}} {{is examined}} to acquire {{information on the}} cause of death inclusive but not limited to manner of death in people dying sudden, unexpected, violent, drug-related, or otherwise suspicious deaths. Digital Autopsy tries to answer the same investigative questions without actual dissection as in a conventional autopsy.|$|E
