50|$|One evening, he {{left his}} home, where he had no {{television}} set, to watch the broadcasting at the TV, he had co-worked. That night, he did not return home. In the morning hours of May 5, 1973, he {{was found dead in}} a street. The <b>forensic</b> <b>autopsy</b> showed no sign of injuries, but it stated death by cerebral hemorrhage. It was assumed that this could be the result of a severe head injury he had suffered during a police raid on the university campus in the chaotic era of March 12, 1971.|$|E
